<DIV><BR><FONT FACE=Arial><FONT COLOR=black SIZE=3>While at The Hartford website, I found this job and thought that you might find it interesting.</FONT><BR><BR>AVP, P&C Enterprise Architecture-0901245<BR><BR><B>Job Description</B><BR><P DIR="ltr" STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px;text-align:left">Overview of the Position</P>
<P DIR="ltr" STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px;text-align:left">Based in Hartford, CT, the Assistant Vice President of Enterprise Architecture will report directly to the Vice President of Property &amp; Casualty CTO for The Hartford and will be responsible for driving architectural strategy, direction, decisions and execution of the P&amp;C Company&#39;s technology plans. This individual will be accountable for all Architectural resources in P&amp;C IT including Lead Line of Business Architects (business segment architects), Domain Architects (e.g. Business Process Management, Portal, Enterprise Content Management, etc.) and Solution Architects that are working on all major initiatives.</P>
<P DIR="ltr" STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px;text-align:left">Additionally, the AVP will be responsible for</P>
<SPAN STYLE="font-family:Arial;font-size:x-small;color:#000000"><SPAN STYLE="font-family:Arial;font-size:x-small;color:#000000"><SPAN STYLE="font-family:Arial;font-size:x-small;color:#000000">driving the Architecture change program over the next few years, evolving the organization to a group that focuses on the full lifecycle of technology management including not only application architecture, but also technical and infrastructure architecture.</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN>
<P DIR="ltr" STYLE="font-weight: bold; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-top: 0px; text-align: left">Responsibilities</P>
<UL>
<LI><B>Ensure optimal architectural decisions, balancing strategic long term needs with tactical, short term realities</B></LI>
<LI><B>Develop an enterprise architecture framework and change management plan</B></LI>
<LI><B>Drive enterprise architecture change management program</B></LI>
<LI><B>Implement architectural metrics measuring transformation progress</B></LI>
<LI><B>Manage architecture resources across projects including resource planning and staffing</B></LI>
<LI><B>Drive Architect Continuum Program, improving architectural skills and overall capability</B></LI>
<LI><B>Manage the architectural governance process</B></LI>
<LI><B>Continue to identify architecture standards</B></LI>
<LI><B>Champion technology simplicity</B></LI>
<LI><B>Work closely with other P&amp;C IT and Business leaders to define overall technology management operating plan</B></LI>
</UL><BR><BR><B>Qualifications</B><BR><P DIR="ltr" STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px;text-align:left">&nbsp;<B><SPAN STYLE="text-decoration:underline">Candidate Profile</SPAN></B></P>
<UL>
<LI>At least 10 years of IT/technology experience, with significant experience defining and implementing architectures across an enterprise required</LI>
<LI>At least 5 years of demonstrated management and leadership experience required; Staff development and supervision (50+ people) required</LI>
<LI>Broad &amp; deep technical knowledge and expertise required</LI>
<LI>Undergraduate degree required, preferably in Computer Science, Management of Information Systems or similar (graduate level degrees a plus)</LI>
<LI>Strong Insurance background a plus</LI>
<LI>Demonstrated track record of project execution and delivery</LI>
<LI>Strong analysis and critical thinking skills</LI>
<LI>Requires dynamic leadership ability that can develop and energize cross-functional multidiscipline, high-performance work</LI>
<LI>Excellent communication skills and experience interacting with senior managers&nbsp;</LI>
<LI>Excellent written and verbal communication&nbsp;</LI>
<LI>Demonstrated ability to influence people at a variety of levels, internally and externally</LI>
<LI>A solid business person, intellectually sharp and energetic, who is dedicated to the improvement of the productivity and profitability of the organization</LI>
<LI>A high energy, results-oriented and resourceful leader who is capable of quickly taking control of his/her responsibilities and establishing himself/herself as a credible and creative business partner</LI>
</UL><BR></FONT></DIV>
